A Quick Rundown of the Shawl Quests:<br>
<br>
Talk to the Loremaster in the temple in the SW corner of Thurg.  <br>
<br>
1st quest:  turn in 4 frost giant toes (uncommon drop off all varieties of frost giant in GD/EW).  Result: ac 1, 1 wis 1 int 1 sv cold shawl<br>
<br>
2nd quest:  get a 10-slot container.  Put 10 frost giant heads (uncommon drop, same mobs) in the box, hit combine. turn in this box and your first shawl to get second shawl. ac 2, 2 wis, 2 int, 2 sv cold.<br>
<br>
3rd quest: The baking quest.  Make master baker first (very easy to do, can be done in about 3 hours and about 50pp).  Talk to loremaster, then modrin (SE corner of the zone, where the oven is).  Kill kodiaks to get meat, make a sandwich, give it and the napkin.  Then kill bunnies and ulthorks for 2nd and 3rd dishes.  Meats for these are not no drop, but the final food product is.  for the 4th recipe, kill snow griffins in EW to get no drop eggs.  4 eggs needed to make the snow griffin souffle.  Giving this to Thoridain along with his napkin will give you the Seal of Thoridain (great range slot item for int/wis casters).  Give seal and 2nd shawl to loremaster and get 3rd shawl and the seal back (not sure if you can use this to multi past this quest for someone else or not.  But it's no drop, so you'd prolly transfer your seal to them if you could multi it.)  3rd shawl:  ac 3, int 3, wis 3, sv cold 3.<br>
<br>
4th shawl:<br>
Collect bricks of velium and crystalline silks from Crystal Caverns. Use pottery skill (another easy one to master) to make a velium vial.  Then collect pieces of velium (also from CC) and use the container the 2nd quest npc gives you to make a Thurgadin gate potion.  Go trigger the wounded guy outside the entrance to Kael Drakkel and give him the gate potion.  Turn in the note he gives you and the 3rd shawl to get the 4th shawl.  ac 4, int 4, wis 4, sv cold 4.<br>
<br>
5th shawl:  Collect threads from Velketor's and bile from shardwurms.  5 threads make a fiber.  3 fibers and a bile make a glowing fiber.  5 glowing fibers and 4th shawl in a tanning kit to try 5th shawl.  If you fail, you are supposed to get 4th shawl back (this is stated by Verant, but not yet confirmed that I know of).  5th shawl is ac 5, wis 5, int 5, sv cold 5.<br>
<br>
6th and 7th shawl are commonly discussed here and info can be found easily.  I don't know them off the top of my head, since I'm still collecting threads.<br>
<br>
Hope this info helps,<br>
-Mallan Southpaw<br>
